&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Service/Ward/Department Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Early Intervention Team provides support and intervention to individuals who are experiencing their first episode of psychosis. The team is based at he John Elliot Unit at Birch Hill Hospital site. The team is multi-disciplinary and is working towards achieving the standards set out within the Department of Health’s paper ‘Achieving Better Access to Mental Health Services by 2020’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide specialist psychological assessment and psychological therapy (cognitive behaviour therapy) and family intervention for people considered to be experiencing an At Risk Mental State (ARMS) and/or First Episode Psychosis (FEP). To provide advice, consultation and supervision as required to other mental health professionals on cognitive behaviour therapy. You will lead on the implementation and development of Family intervention services in HMR EIT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities of the Post:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carry out specialist psychological assessments to identify individuals considered to be at; high risk of developing a serious mental health problem using the Comprehensive Assessment of At-Risk Mental States (CAARMS) and/or to have developed a psychotic illness (PANSS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide evidence based psychological therapies (CBT/FI) for those with ARMS, FEP and their carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work closely within the Early Intervention Team to manage the psychological referrals in the most effective way and to contribute to developing an increased awareness, knowledge and application of psychological interventions within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Requirements of the Person Specification:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good degree (2:1 or above) in psychology &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt; a post graduate doctorate in clinical psychology or a good degree/diploma (2:1 or above) in nursing, social work or occupational therapy and a specialist cognitive therapy qualification (e.g. PGDip or MSc in Cognitive Behaviour Therapy). Accredited or working towards accreditation with BABCP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of delivery of cognitive behaviour therapy to people experiencing psychosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use of a car or access to a means of mobility to travel across the Trust is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
